Second terrorist attack rips through Damascus on 6th anniversary of Syrian Uprising
BEIRUT, LEBANON (3:05 P.M.) â€“ Minutes ago, another terrorist attack was reported inside the Syrian capital of Damascus, marking the second time today a massive explosion has targeted civilians in the city.
According to an Al-Masdar field correspondent in Damascus, the second terrorist attack took place the Rabwah area, causing a loud explosion that could be heard from all over the Syrian capital.
This terrorist attack followed the prior suicide bombing that struck the Justice Palace in the Al-Hamidiyah Quarter, which killed 31 civilians and wounded over 60 other bystanders in this popular area.
No further details have been released.
March 15th marks the 6th anniversary of the Syrian Uprising that saw the country descend into a brutal war.